A simple pasta dish that's packed with flavour.

== Pasta ==

Boil a large #pot of @water{to taste} with @salt{to taste} for the @dried rigatoni{180%grams}.

When boiling, add the rigatoni to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve a cup of cooking water then drain in a #colander and pop back in the #pot, off the heat.

Mix the @creme fraiche{65%grams}, a dash of cooking water and the @sun dried tomato paste{1%sachet} through the pasta. Season with @pepper{to taste}.

== Chorizo ==

Halve the @cherry tomatoes{250%grams}.

Roughly chop the @olives{1%sachet}.

Place a #pan over medium heat (no oil).

Once the pan is hot, add the @chorizo{90%grams} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the pan and keep aside.

== To Serve ==

Divide the pasta between bowls or deep plates.

Garnish with chorizo, cherry tomatoes and olives.

> Add a splash of @?oil{1%tbsp} if desired for extra richness.